FBIS3-55024 "drsov003_v_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 Lithuania Crack Forces Shutdown of Ignalina Turbine WS0401193494 Tallinn BNS in English 1616 GMT 4 Jan 94 WS0401193494 Tallinn BNS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vilnius, Jan 04, BNS -- The Ignalina nuclear power plant, Lithuania's chief electricity producer, shut down New Year's eve one out of two turbines of the first nuclear reactor, the RESPUBLIKA newspaper said. The stoppage reportedly resulted from a crack in the turbine's pipe system. Repairs will presumably be completed Jan. 10. The reactor will continue to operate with one turbine until then. Experts said the shut down of one turbine will not have any noticeable effect on the country's energy system.
